NOTE /SegmentIndex

                                                                                                                                                                                            


1
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:11.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[muffled shouting]

2
00:00:11.636 --> 00:00:13.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look, save your energy.

3
00:00:13.513 --> 00:00:16.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have you out of there
as soon as possible.

4
00:00:17.809 --> 00:00:19.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope.

5
00:00:21.896 --> 00:00:23.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try rerouting
the power coupling.

6
00:00:28.111 --> 00:00:29.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

7
00:00:29.863 --> 00:00:32.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can activate
the interlock servos.

8
00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:33.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mr. O'Brien.

9
00:00:33.783 --> 00:00:37.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, those people
have been stuck in that air lock

10
00:00:37.537 --> 00:00:38.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for over an hour.

11
00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:41.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, if you can wait
till we get that door opened

12
00:00:41.249 --> 00:00:43.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll be happy to listen
to any problems you might have.

13
00:00:43.585 --> 00:00:46.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I've already been waiting two days
for your people to readjust

14
00:00:46.463 --> 00:00:48.631 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
my ship's antimatter flow converter.

15
00:00:48.715 --> 00:00:51.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm afraid we've gotten a little behind
in our maintenance schedule.

16
00:00:51.843 --> 00:00:53.553 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not interested in hearing excuses.

17
00:00:53.636 --> 00:00:56.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I have a shipment of Tamen Sahsheer
waiting to be delivered to Largo V,

18
00:00:57.015 --> 00:01:00.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I'll need to do better than warp 1
to get there before it spoils.

19
00:01:00.185 --> 00:01:04.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll try to get a repair crew
to you by the end of the day.

20
00:01:04.105 --> 00:01:05.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, that's the best I can do.

21
00:01:05.607 --> 00:01:08.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Your best, Mr. O'Brien,
hardly seems good enough.

22
00:01:11.946 --> 00:01:13.573 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> Dax to O'Brien.</i>

23
00:01:13.656 --> 00:01:15.200 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien here.

24
00:01:15.283 --> 00:01:16.493 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Can you spare a minute, Chief?</i>

25
00:01:16.576 --> 00:01:18.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have a little problem here at the lab.</i>

26
00:01:20.371 --> 00:01:22.123 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

27
00:01:27.921 --> 00:01:29.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thanks for coming, Chief.

28
00:01:29.380 --> 00:01:31.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing out here?

29
00:01:33.635 --> 00:01:35.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[loud whining]

30
00:01:38.598 --> 00:01:40.642 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you checked the EPS converter?

31
00:01:40.725 --> 00:01:42.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, first thing.

32
00:01:42.352 --> 00:01:44.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How about the intensity grid?
-It's fine.

33
00:01:44.813 --> 00:01:47.607 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then it's probably the secondary
phase modulator.

34
00:01:47.690 --> 00:01:50.860 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We had trouble with them last week
in the main power core.

35
00:01:53.238 --> 00:01:54.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should do it.

36
00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:55.865 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[noise stops]

37
00:01:59.994 --> 00:02:01.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Anything else I can do for you?

38
00:02:04.124 --> 00:02:07.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The navigational computer
hasn't worked reliably for three days.

39
00:02:07.752 --> 00:02:10.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I ask for the star charts
for the Argosian sector--

40
00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:12.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Glessene sector
comes up instead.

41
00:02:13.091 --> 00:02:15.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's when I can coax
this system on line.

42
00:02:15.844 --> 00:02:17.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[O'Brien] Uh-huh.

43
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:19.055 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try it now.

44
00:02:21.057 --> 00:02:23.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Huh! That's more like it.

45
00:02:33.570 --> 00:02:35.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You look like you
could use some sleep.

46
00:02:35.989 --> 00:02:37.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who has time for sleep?

47
00:02:38.366 --> 00:02:41.327 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd settle for five minutes
peace and quiet.

48
00:02:44.831 --> 00:02:47.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Chief, I thought you were going
to fix the replicators.

49
00:02:48.626 --> 00:02:50.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're absolutely right, sir.

50
00:02:50.962 --> 00:02:52.422 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew I'd forgotten something.

51
00:02:52.672 --> 00:02:55.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Can't have the Operations Chief
sitting around daydreaming

52
00:02:55.425 --> 00:02:57.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
when there's work
to be done, can we?

53
00:02:57.510 --> 00:02:59.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ho, ho, ho, ho.
I'll get right on it.

54
00:03:02.307 --> 00:03:04.684 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"Fix the replicators, Chief."

55
00:03:04.767 --> 00:03:06.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"My console's off-line, Chief."

56
00:03:06.811 --> 00:03:08.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

57
00:03:08.313 --> 00:03:10.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I should have transferred
to a cargo drone--

58
00:03:10.940 --> 00:03:13.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no people, no complaints.

59
00:03:35.757 --> 00:03:37.175 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

60
00:03:45.183 --> 00:03:46.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[instrument humming]

61
00:03:53.566 --> 00:03:55.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hot coffee-- black, double sweet.

62
00:04:26.891 --> 00:04:28.977 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[beeping]

63
00:06:26.511 --> 00:06:28.137 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Tell me, Quark.

64
00:06:28.221 --> 00:06:32.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I mistaken, or is business
a little slow today?

65
00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:36.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Slow? It's been almost nonexistent
for the past three days.

66
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:39.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Mmm. Who knows?

67
00:06:39.982 --> 00:06:43.820 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If things don't improve
you may be forced to close down.

68
00:06:43.903 --> 00:06:45.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Oh, you'd like that, wouldn't you?

69
00:06:45.613 --> 00:06:50.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, let's just say, without you around
my job would be considerably easier.

70
00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:53.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Without me around,
you'd be forced to find

71
00:06:53.704 --> 00:06:56.541 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
some other poor innocent to persecute.

72
00:06:56.624 --> 00:07:01.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Think about that while you sit here
gloating at my misfortune.

73
00:07:01.087 --> 00:07:02.171 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Quark!

74
00:07:02.255 --> 00:07:04.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
You call this Kohlian stew?

75
00:07:10.513 --> 00:07:15.643 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
If your meal isn't satisfactory
I'm sure we could, uh, exchange it

76
00:07:15.726 --> 00:07:17.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
for something more to your liking.

77
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:22.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Aren't you the least bit curious
as to how it tastes?

78
00:07:24.902 --> 00:07:27.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
[groaning]

79
00:07:27.530 --> 00:07:28.823 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Now...

80
00:07:28.906 --> 00:07:30.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
you served it.

81
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:31.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're going to eat it.

82
00:07:31.701 --> 00:07:33.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, that's enough.

83
00:07:34.787 --> 00:07:36.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said, eat it!

84
00:07:38.166 --> 00:07:39.667 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I said...

85
00:07:40.293 --> 00:07:41.794 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
that's enough.

86
00:07:42.462 --> 00:07:43.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Leave him alone.

87
00:07:48.634 --> 00:07:52.305 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:10.00% 
Well, another satisfied customer.

88
00:07:54.223 --> 00:07:56.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's these replicators.

89
00:07:56.434 --> 00:07:59.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If I don't get them fixed soon,
they'll destroy my business.

90
00:07:59.103 --> 00:08:00.980 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why not get O'Brien to fix them?

91
00:08:01.063 --> 00:08:04.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He has the replicators on
the command level working perfectly.

92
00:08:04.484 --> 00:08:06.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm on his waiting list.

93
00:08:06.861 --> 00:08:09.822 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He assures me he'll get to them
as soon as he can.

94
00:08:10.239 --> 00:08:11.532 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Mmm...

95
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:13.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No telling when that will be.

96
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Chief's a very busy man.

97
00:08:21.292 --> 00:08:22.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

98
00:08:23.669 --> 00:08:25.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display a station layout.

99
00:08:27.256 --> 00:08:30.760 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Highlight locations
of all repaired replicators

100
00:08:30.843 --> 00:08:32.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
on command level.

101
00:08:32.428 --> 00:08:33.596 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on machine]
<i>Information restricted</i>

102
00:08:33.679 --> 00:08:36.140 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>to security clearance 5 and above.</i>

103
00:08:36.224 --> 00:08:38.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Please enter security verification.</i>

104
00:08:54.575 --> 00:08:56.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Clearance verified.</i>

105
00:09:08.714 --> 00:09:09.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There you go, sir.

106
00:09:10.007 --> 00:09:12.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I think you'll find that
more to your liking.

107
00:09:13.094 --> 00:09:15.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very much appreciated, Mr. O'Brien.

108
00:09:15.388 --> 00:09:16.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Don't mention it, sir.

109
00:09:16.514 --> 00:09:18.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unfortunately,
there are plenty of replicators

110
00:09:18.474 --> 00:09:20.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
around the station
that still need looking after.

111
00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:22.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You all right, Chief?

112
00:09:23.563 --> 00:09:25.106 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm just a bit hot.

113
00:09:25.648 --> 00:09:28.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The environmental controls
must be acting up again.

114
00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:29.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Send my regards to Mrs. O'Brien.

115
00:09:29.902 --> 00:09:31.654 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake tells me she's a wonderful teacher.

116
00:09:31.737 --> 00:09:33.447 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, that's nice to hear, sir.

117
00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:35.241 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's flower units about the lad herself.

118
00:09:35.324 --> 00:09:36.784 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

119
00:09:36.867 --> 00:09:37.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

120
00:09:37.910 --> 00:09:39.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that you just said?

121
00:09:40.454 --> 00:09:44.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's... quite fond of the lad herself.

122
00:09:44.917 --> 00:09:46.168 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

123
00:09:46.252 --> 00:09:47.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm glad to hear it.

124
00:09:47.920 --> 00:09:49.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Very good, sir.

125
00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:58.973 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Ladies.

126
00:09:59.056 --> 00:10:00.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello, Lieutenant.

127
00:10:01.601 --> 00:10:04.228 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I forgot how different it was.

128
00:10:04.312 --> 00:10:05.938 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How different what was?

129
00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:07.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Being female.

130
00:10:07.940 --> 00:10:09.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't been one for over 80 years.

131
00:10:10.776 --> 00:10:11.861 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All this attention.

132
00:10:11.944 --> 00:10:13.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Imagine it must take
some getting used to.

133
00:10:13.779 --> 00:10:15.448 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Actually, I find it quite enjoyable.

134
00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:16.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major Kira.

135
00:10:16.991 --> 00:10:18.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant Dax.

136
00:10:19.035 --> 00:10:22.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'd be honored to have you
join my little party--

137
00:10:22.496 --> 00:10:24.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
as my guests, of course.

138
00:10:24.123 --> 00:10:25.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's all this, Quark?

139
00:10:25.791 --> 00:10:28.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You cheat your 1,000th customer?

140
00:10:28.127 --> 00:10:30.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Who says Bajorans
don't have a sense of humor?

141
00:10:31.255 --> 00:10:36.302 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Actually, uh, we're celebrating the repair
of the bar's replicator system.

142
00:10:36.886 --> 00:10:39.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps I could interest you

143
00:10:39.597 --> 00:10:43.434 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in a nice, double-whipped,
I'danian spice pudding.

144
00:10:43.768 --> 00:10:45.394 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, what do you think?

145
00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think I'm due back at Ops

146
00:10:47.647 --> 00:10:49.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but, uh, go on.

147
00:10:49.148 --> 00:10:50.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Enjoy yourself.

148
00:11:02.787 --> 00:11:03.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief?

149
00:11:04.622 --> 00:11:06.165 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[slurring] How can I help you, Major?

150
00:11:08.542 --> 00:11:10.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Looks like you're the one
who could use a little help.

151
00:11:11.420 --> 00:11:13.381 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, no, I'm fine, really.

152
00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:19.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I suppose this isn't
a good time to tell you

153
00:11:19.762 --> 00:11:22.139 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that number three turbolift
has broken down again.

154
00:11:26.477 --> 00:11:28.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Joking, Chief.

155
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:31.899 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, lark's true pepper.

156
00:11:32.566 --> 00:11:33.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

157
00:11:36.737 --> 00:11:39.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let birds go further loose maybe.

158
00:11:40.699 --> 00:11:41.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Shout easy play.

159
00:11:41.992 --> 00:11:44.703 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, you're not making any sense.

160
00:11:44.787 --> 00:11:46.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Round the turbulent quick.

161
00:11:51.168 --> 00:11:53.337 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, close the reverse harbor.

162
00:11:57.216 --> 00:12:00.428 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A-Ankle try sound.

163
00:12:01.137 --> 00:12:02.847 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Reset gleaming.

164
00:12:05.099 --> 00:12:06.475 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
D-Dinner to bug.

165
00:12:09.687 --> 00:12:11.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief, wait.

166
00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:13.065 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
When?

167
00:12:13.149 --> 00:12:14.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chief.

168
00:12:27.288 --> 00:12:30.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, continue neural imaging scan

169
00:12:30.666 --> 00:12:32.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and stimulate visual cortex.

170
00:12:32.501 --> 00:12:35.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female automated voice]
<i>All visual responses normal.</i>

171
00:12:40.301 --> 00:12:41.927 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Begin auditory stimuli.

172
00:12:42.261 --> 00:12:44.180 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[woman]<i> No physiological damage.</i>

173
00:12:44.263 --> 00:12:46.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>All brain functions</i>
<i>within normal parameters.</i>

174
00:12:48.893 --> 00:12:50.519 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Nurse.
-Yes?

175
00:12:51.312 --> 00:12:53.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Will you pull up Mr. O'Brien's
neurophysiological history, please?

176
00:12:54.064 --> 00:12:54.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, Doctor.

177
00:13:03.574 --> 00:13:05.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is that? What's he written?

178
00:13:05.493 --> 00:13:06.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I wish I knew.

179
00:13:07.912 --> 00:13:11.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Strike limits flame the dark true salt.

180
00:13:11.332 --> 00:13:12.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please, Chief, take a seat.

181
00:13:12.708 --> 00:13:14.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link complete.

182
00:13:14.502 --> 00:13:16.003 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Way link!

183
00:13:19.256 --> 00:13:20.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's wrong with him?

184
00:13:20.883 --> 00:13:23.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He appears to suffering
from a form of aphasia.

185
00:13:23.344 --> 00:13:24.637 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a perceptual dysfunction

186
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:28.390 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
in which aural and visual stimuli
are incorrectly processed by the brain.

187
00:13:28.474 --> 00:13:30.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His actual thinking hasn't been affected

188
00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:32.561 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but he's incapable of expressing himself

189
00:13:32.645 --> 00:13:34.605 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
or understanding others.

190
00:13:35.231 --> 00:13:38.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Victory strike limits frosted wake.

191
00:13:39.985 --> 00:13:42.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Simple hesitation!

192
00:13:43.197 --> 00:13:44.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not sure I follow you, Doctor.

193
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:46.450 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You say Mr. O'Brien is aphasiac

194
00:13:46.534 --> 00:13:47.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but all of his tests
have come up negative.

195
00:13:49.703 --> 00:13:53.457 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Isn't aphasia typically associated
with some kind of cranial trauma?

196
00:13:53.832 --> 00:13:57.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yes. It can occur as a result of a stroke
or a blow to the head.

197
00:13:57.378 --> 00:13:58.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But there's no evidence of that here.

198
00:13:58.921 --> 00:14:01.382 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Did you check the medical library
for any precedents?

199
00:14:01.465 --> 00:14:04.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And rechecked-- nothing, so far.

200
00:14:04.552 --> 00:14:05.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have any theories?

201
00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:07.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not yet.

202
00:14:07.846 --> 00:14:09.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Find one.

203
00:14:09.473 --> 00:14:12.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira, get a hold
of the Chief's personal duty log.

204
00:14:12.184 --> 00:14:15.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I want to know where he's been
and what he's done for the past 52 hours.

205
00:14:15.187 --> 00:14:18.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've already examined it, Commander.
He's been all over this station.

206
00:14:18.607 --> 00:14:21.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Retrace his steps and see what
you come up with.

207
00:14:21.485 --> 00:14:25.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Dax, you will temporarily assume
Mr. O'Brien's duties.

208
00:14:25.155 --> 00:14:27.032 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, uh... Um...

209
00:14:27.116 --> 00:14:28.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is there a problem, Lieutenant?

210
00:14:30.119 --> 00:14:31.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lieutenant?

211
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:35.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sorry, Benjamin.

212
00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:37.793 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm unable to...

213
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:42.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
foolish assembled regal...

214
00:14:42.631 --> 00:14:44.383 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control weather.

215
00:14:55.185 --> 00:14:59.356 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Spontaneous development of aphasia
is virtually impossible.

216
00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:02.818 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Yet we saw Lieutenant Dax
become aphasiac before our eyes.

217
00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:04.486 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This told me we were
dealing with a disease

218
00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:06.155 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
which only mimics aphasia,

219
00:15:07.364 --> 00:15:10.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
so I ran a full neural synaptic comparison
between Dax and O'Brien

220
00:15:10.826 --> 00:15:13.245 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and I found this in the temporal lobes
of both patients.

221
00:15:13.537 --> 00:15:14.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A virus.

222
00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:17.708 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It imposes itself
within the established synaptic pathways

223
00:15:17.791 --> 00:15:19.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and then randomly reroutes them.

224
00:15:19.752 --> 00:15:22.379 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For example, when I look at this,

225
00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:25.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
a process occurs within my brain

226
00:15:25.090 --> 00:15:27.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
which connects the stimulus
to the word "tricorder."

227
00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:29.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus disrupts that process.

228
00:15:30.262 --> 00:15:32.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd see a tricorder

229
00:15:32.181 --> 00:15:34.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I'd say something ridiculous,
like "window."

230
00:15:35.059 --> 00:15:36.268 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Exactly.

231
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:37.895 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I think you should get over here.

232
00:15:37.978 --> 00:15:39.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Night the flow trade again.
-You lost pile luck.

233
00:15:40.022 --> 00:15:42.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Away tunnel back the garden.

234
00:15:42.107 --> 00:15:43.943 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor, I want this station

235
00:15:44.026 --> 00:15:46.111 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
put under emergency quarantine
immediately.

236
00:15:46.195 --> 00:15:47.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

237
00:15:51.825 --> 00:15:54.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[conversation and music]

238
00:15:54.828 --> 00:15:55.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man] Dabo!

239
00:15:56.038 --> 00:15:57.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[shouting]

240
00:16:03.420 --> 00:16:07.841 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what is going on here?

241
00:16:07.925 --> 00:16:09.385 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does it look like?

242
00:16:09.510 --> 00:16:11.845 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It looks like business as usual

243
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.263 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but that's impossible

244
00:16:13.347 --> 00:16:16.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because all shops and businesses
have been closed until further notice.

245
00:16:16.892 --> 00:16:19.853 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Except, of course,
for essential station operations.

246
00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:22.439 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
For which this place hardly qualifies.

247
00:16:22.523 --> 00:16:23.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't think they'd agree.

248
00:16:24.024 --> 00:16:26.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This quarantine has everybody
on edge, Constable.

249
00:16:27.069 --> 00:16:30.280 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Would you deprive them
of a little harmless diversion?

250
00:16:34.743 --> 00:16:37.746 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They'd be safer in their quarters.

251
00:16:38.122 --> 00:16:41.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, this Kohlian stew-- magnificent.

252
00:16:42.251 --> 00:16:45.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Fortunately, my assistant, Rom,
was able to fix the replicators.

253
00:16:48.132 --> 00:16:52.219 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes... Very fortunate.

254
00:17:10.070 --> 00:17:11.321 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] Jake...

255
00:17:11.405 --> 00:17:13.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I expected you home an hour ago.

256
00:17:13.198 --> 00:17:14.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sorry. I was at Nog's.

257
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:17.119 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dad, about this quarantine--

258
00:17:17.202 --> 00:17:18.620 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it's going to be OK, isn't it?

259
00:17:18.704 --> 00:17:20.414 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's just a precaution, nothing more.

260
00:17:20.497 --> 00:17:22.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Jaheel] I wish I shared your
confidence, Commander.

261
00:17:23.625 --> 00:17:25.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go straight home, son.

262
00:17:25.169 --> 00:17:26.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll see you at dinner.

263
00:17:27.838 --> 00:17:31.216 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain Jaheel, all visitors
have been confined to their ships.

264
00:17:31.300 --> 00:17:33.427 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Believe me,
there is no place I'd rather be.

265
00:17:33.510 --> 00:17:34.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then what are you doing here?

266
00:17:35.345 --> 00:17:38.599 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, I officially request permission
to leave this station.

267
00:17:38.682 --> 00:17:39.725 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Request denied.

268
00:17:39.808 --> 00:17:42.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But none of my crew
has been affected by this virus of yours.

269
00:17:42.519 --> 00:17:46.190 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And unless I depart at once
my whole cargo will be ruined!

270
00:17:46.273 --> 00:17:50.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, I suggest
you return to your ship now.

271
00:17:51.779 --> 00:17:56.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Please. I don't want to get sick.

272
00:17:56.867 --> 00:18:01.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm sorry, but until we can
find a cure for this... thing,

273
00:18:01.163 --> 00:18:02.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one's going anywhere.

274
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:26.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer,

275
00:18:27.356 --> 00:18:32.194 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
let's start with one
Ferengi Starduster, please.

276
00:18:32.277 --> 00:18:33.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Extra strong.

277
00:18:41.995 --> 00:18:43.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfect.

278
00:18:48.168 --> 00:18:51.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Uh... I thought the front wheels
were sticking a bit.

279
00:18:51.964 --> 00:18:56.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unauthorized access
to crew quarters is a crime, Quark.

280
00:18:56.343 --> 00:18:59.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You could have just asked
to use the replicators.

281
00:18:59.888 --> 00:19:03.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's an old Ferengi saying--
"Never ask when you can take."

282
00:19:04.476 --> 00:19:06.687 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, how did you figure it out?

283
00:19:07.104 --> 00:19:10.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You claimed Rom fixed your replicators.

284
00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:11.984 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So?
-Rom's an idiot.

285
00:19:12.067 --> 00:19:14.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He couldn't fix a straw if it was bent.

286
00:19:14.903 --> 00:19:17.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're right. Rom is an idiot.

287
00:19:18.448 --> 00:19:20.909 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Remind me to get rid of him tomorrow.

288
00:19:23.829 --> 00:19:26.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Based on the levels of the virus
found in the patients' blood,

289
00:19:26.832 --> 00:19:28.959 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it's being
absorbed through ingestion.

290
00:19:29.042 --> 00:19:30.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're saying it's in our food?
-Well, that's not possible.

291
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:34.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
All the food on this station is replicated
and all the replicators use biofilters.

292
00:19:35.048 --> 00:19:38.260 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They automatically screen out contaminants
including viruses.

293
00:19:38.343 --> 00:19:42.014 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I've analyzed samples
from replicators all over the station.

294
00:19:42.639 --> 00:19:44.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Food on the command level is contaminated.

295
00:19:44.641 --> 00:19:46.935 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But all of us here have
eaten from those replicators.

296
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:48.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How come we're not aphasic?

297
00:19:48.353 --> 00:19:50.105 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is highly adaptable.

298
00:19:50.230 --> 00:19:53.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Its incubation period
seems to vary within each individual.

299
00:19:54.026 --> 00:19:56.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
According to O'Brien's duty log

300
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:58.363 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the last thing he did
before becoming aphasic

301
00:19:58.447 --> 00:20:00.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
was fix the command level replicators.

302
00:20:00.616 --> 00:20:03.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get a repair crew over there
to inspect the site.

303
00:20:03.785 --> 00:20:05.537 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's shut down those replicators.

304
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:08.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Maybe we'll be able
to limit further contamination.

305
00:20:08.165 --> 00:20:10.375 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm afraid that's not going to do it, sir.

306
00:20:10.459 --> 00:20:13.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been getting aphasic patients
from all over the station.

307
00:20:13.337 --> 00:20:14.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is that possible?

308
00:20:14.588 --> 00:20:15.714 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can thank Quark.

309
00:20:15.797 --> 00:20:19.009 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I caught him using a replicator
in one of the vacant crew quarters.

310
00:20:19.092 --> 00:20:21.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was producing
his entire menu out of there.

311
00:20:23.555 --> 00:20:25.682 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If this virus is present

312
00:20:26.433 --> 00:20:29.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
within a large enough segment
of the population

313
00:20:29.770 --> 00:20:31.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
it could mean...

314
00:20:32.522 --> 00:20:34.107 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Doctor?

315
00:20:35.442 --> 00:20:37.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I just took an air sample.

316
00:20:39.279 --> 00:20:40.948 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko] The virus...

317
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:43.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's mutated into an airborne variety.

318
00:20:43.116 --> 00:20:44.326 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means?

319
00:20:44.576 --> 00:20:47.996 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which means the whole station is infected.

320
00:20:57.256 --> 00:21:00.801 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46423.7.</i>

321
00:21:00.884 --> 00:21:05.222 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Nearly 60% of DS9's population</i>
<i>has now contracted the aphasia virus.</i>

322
00:21:05.305 --> 00:21:07.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've initiated standard</i>
<i>quarantine procedures</i>

323
00:21:07.808 --> 00:21:09.559 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>and are advising all incoming ships</i>

324
00:21:09.643 --> 00:21:11.436 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>to maintain their distance</i>
<i>from the station</i>

325
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:13.230 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>until further notice.</i>

326
00:21:34.001 --> 00:21:37.838 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I found it in the replicator's
pattern generator.

327
00:21:37.921 --> 00:21:40.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
O'Brien must have accidentally
triggered it when he repaired the system.

328
00:21:40.882 --> 00:21:44.928 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
According to Bashir, it introduced
an anomalous programming sequence

329
00:21:45.012 --> 00:21:47.097 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into the materialization subroutine.

330
00:21:47.180 --> 00:21:49.099 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In effect, it built the virus

331
00:21:49.182 --> 00:21:52.686 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
directly into the replicated food
at a molecular level.

332
00:21:52.769 --> 00:21:55.397 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-So what we have here is sabotage.
-Cardassian sabotage.

333
00:21:55.480 --> 00:21:58.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How can you be sure?
-Has a diboridium core for a power source.

334
00:21:58.608 --> 00:22:00.569 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That is Cardassian technology.

335
00:22:01.028 --> 00:22:03.113 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[man]<i> Bashir to Sisko.</i>

336
00:22:03.739 --> 00:22:05.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko here.

337
00:22:05.157 --> 00:22:07.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[man]<i> Commander, I think you'd better</i>
<i>get down here to the infirmary</i>

338
00:22:07.367 --> 00:22:08.452 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>as soon as possible.</i>

339
00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:09.619 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On my way.

340
00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:17.627 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, Doctor?

341
00:22:19.796 --> 00:22:21.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake?

342
00:22:22.007 --> 00:22:25.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Left... become better...

343
00:22:25.135 --> 00:22:28.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
control... entire hope.

344
00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:33.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Bashir] We've converted
some empty crew quarters

345
00:22:33.560 --> 00:22:34.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
into a hospital ward.

346
00:22:34.686 --> 00:22:35.729 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He'll be well looked after.

347
00:22:35.812 --> 00:22:37.647 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll take him there myself.

348
00:22:38.190 --> 00:22:40.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, Jake.
You're going to be all right.

349
00:22:40.317 --> 00:22:44.821 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Commander, when you've got a moment,
I've found something I'd like to show you.

350
00:22:49.326 --> 00:22:50.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[people muttering]

351
00:22:50.660 --> 00:22:53.246 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] It'll be all right.
Just lay back.

352
00:22:53.330 --> 00:22:54.498 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[coughing]

353
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:56.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman] I know,
but just lay back and relax.

354
00:22:59.252 --> 00:23:02.464 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] Food... dabo... drinks...

355
00:23:02.547 --> 00:23:05.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
money... hand... mine... give!

356
00:23:06.051 --> 00:23:09.971 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Well, Quark, I see even you couldn't
weasel your way clear of this one.

357
00:23:10.055 --> 00:23:13.016 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You underestimate the Ferengi
immune system, Commander.

358
00:23:13.100 --> 00:23:15.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'm merely here visiting
my less fortunate customers

359
00:23:15.852 --> 00:23:17.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to make sure they're
not faking the illness

360
00:23:17.729 --> 00:23:19.189 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
to avoid paying their bills.

361
00:23:19.272 --> 00:23:20.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No one could be that devious.

362
00:23:20.857 --> 00:23:21.817 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am.

363
00:23:21.900 --> 00:23:25.737 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You... gold... owe... me!

364
00:23:28.532 --> 00:23:30.617 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[indistinct conversation]

365
00:23:30.784 --> 00:23:33.286 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark] I... now... give...

366
00:23:33.954 --> 00:23:35.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Up!

367
00:23:37.999 --> 00:23:39.668 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're doing everything possible.

368
00:23:43.296 --> 00:23:44.840 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be back as soon as I can.

369
00:23:52.597 --> 00:23:54.724 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The virus is synthetic, Commander.

370
00:23:54.808 --> 00:23:57.102 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Its nucleotide sequence is too perfect.

371
00:23:57.185 --> 00:23:58.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's clearly not natural.

372
00:23:58.728 --> 00:24:01.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're saying the Cardassians
genetically engineered this thing?

373
00:24:01.606 --> 00:24:03.024 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I thought at first,

374
00:24:03.108 --> 00:24:05.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I've studied Cardassian
genetic engineering.

375
00:24:05.318 --> 00:24:07.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They always build distinctive
monoclonial links into their DNA.

376
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:09.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus has none of those features.

377
00:24:10.115 --> 00:24:11.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right, then who made it?

378
00:24:11.408 --> 00:24:12.701 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well, that's what I wanted to find out.

379
00:24:12.784 --> 00:24:15.120 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
So I referenced all known
DNA construction techniques

380
00:24:15.203 --> 00:24:16.663 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the Federation records

381
00:24:16.746 --> 00:24:18.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and this protein series was the key.

382
00:24:19.332 --> 00:24:20.333 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It indicates--

383
00:24:20.458 --> 00:24:22.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Doctor! Who created this virus?

384
00:24:22.627 --> 00:24:24.045 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The Bajorans, sir.

385
00:24:24.671 --> 00:24:26.339 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I believe it must have been
a terrorist plot

386
00:24:26.464 --> 00:24:28.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to sabotage the Cardassians
while they were here.

387
00:24:34.472 --> 00:24:36.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The energy decay of the power core

388
00:24:36.349 --> 00:24:39.644 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
indicates it dates back
to the building of the station.

389
00:24:39.728 --> 00:24:41.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] That's 18 years ago.

390
00:24:41.855 --> 00:24:43.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suppose the Bajoran underground

391
00:24:43.607 --> 00:24:46.234 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
could have smuggled it aboard
during construction...

392
00:24:46.318 --> 00:24:49.196 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before I took over as Head of Security.

393
00:24:49.571 --> 00:24:51.740 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But why would the underground
go to all the trouble

394
00:24:51.823 --> 00:24:53.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
of planting a booby trap
and not set it off?

395
00:24:53.992 --> 00:24:55.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Maybe they forgot.

396
00:24:55.452 --> 00:24:59.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No. More likely, they were captured
or killed before they could release it.

397
00:24:59.789 --> 00:25:02.417 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We need to find out
who created this virus.

398
00:25:02.959 --> 00:25:04.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're our best hope.

399
00:25:05.086 --> 00:25:08.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing] 18 years is a long time.

400
00:25:09.007 --> 00:25:13.303 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Besides, even if she finds who did this,
that's no guarantee they can help us.

401
00:25:13.386 --> 00:25:15.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just have to hope
they remember the antidote.

402
00:25:15.722 --> 00:25:18.433 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's assuming they ever
bothered to create one.

403
00:25:26.816 --> 00:25:28.526 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It had to be someone
in the underground

404
00:25:28.610 --> 00:25:30.195 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
familiar with genetic engineering.

405
00:25:30.278 --> 00:25:31.738 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Galis]<i> Eighteen years ago?</i>

406
00:25:31.905 --> 00:25:34.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Sounds like something Dekon Elig</i>
<i>might have thought up.</i>

407
00:25:34.574 --> 00:25:35.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How can I find him?

408
00:25:36.034 --> 00:25:38.328 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>The last I heard</i>
<i>he was in a Cardassian prison.</i>

409
00:25:38.536 --> 00:25:39.704 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where was he being held?

410
00:25:40.205 --> 00:25:42.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>The Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>

411
00:25:42.290 --> 00:25:45.085 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>but that was nine years ago.</i>

412
00:25:47.587 --> 00:25:49.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And you have no idea where he is now?

413
00:25:50.006 --> 00:25:51.967 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Think, Galis! This is important.

414
00:25:52.425 --> 00:25:56.680 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I'm sorry, Kira,</i>
<i>but it was all so long ago.</i>

415
00:26:02.394 --> 00:26:03.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is it, Jake?

416
00:26:03.812 --> 00:26:05.730 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when life.

417
00:26:05.814 --> 00:26:07.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Roll linger when...

418
00:26:07.315 --> 00:26:08.650 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What?

419
00:26:15.448 --> 00:26:18.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Other support, strong courage...

420
00:26:20.287 --> 00:26:21.997 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

421
00:26:24.165 --> 00:26:25.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's running a high fever.

422
00:26:26.334 --> 00:26:27.711 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way long.

423
00:26:27.794 --> 00:26:28.837 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Open way.

424
00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:34.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Doctor, we have an emergency
in crew quarters.

425
00:26:49.399 --> 00:26:50.692 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How is he, Doctor?

426
00:26:50.775 --> 00:26:52.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not good, I'm afraid.

427
00:26:52.485 --> 00:26:54.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The virus has attacked
his autonomic nervous system.

428
00:26:55.071 --> 00:26:56.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Can he be stabilized?

429
00:26:56.573 --> 00:26:58.575 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He hasn't responded to neural stimulation.

430
00:26:59.034 --> 00:27:02.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've given him 30cc's of corophizine
to avoid secondary infection,

431
00:27:02.454 --> 00:27:04.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but so far, I've been unable
to lower his fever.

432
00:27:04.831 --> 00:27:06.624 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are his chances?

433
00:27:08.251 --> 00:27:11.713 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Unless I find some way
to counteract the virus,

434
00:27:12.422 --> 00:27:14.049 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he'll be dead in 12 hours.

435
00:27:15.133 --> 00:27:17.010 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have you made any progress?

436
00:27:17.093 --> 00:27:18.345 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No.

437
00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:21.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've tried base pair destabilizers,

438
00:27:21.139 --> 00:27:24.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
sequential disruption--
nothing seems to affect it.

439
00:27:25.352 --> 00:27:28.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir, I've got seven other aphasic patients

440
00:27:28.897 --> 00:27:31.524 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
displaying the same symptoms
as O'Brien here,

441
00:27:31.816 --> 00:27:34.027 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I'm afraid this is only the beginning.

442
00:27:34.736 --> 00:27:36.613 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Keep searching, Doctor.

443
00:27:36.696 --> 00:27:41.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I hope Major Kira finds whoever's
responsible for creating this virus.

444
00:27:41.618 --> 00:27:44.162 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd like to meet that person myself.

445
00:27:44.245 --> 00:27:46.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This virus is a work of genius.

446
00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:48.833 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll try to arrange it for you.

447
00:27:59.677 --> 00:28:02.389 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[womanr]<i> Link established with</i>
<i>the Bajoran Archival Records.</i>

448
00:28:02.472 --> 00:28:05.058 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Locate files on Velos VII Internment Camp.

449
00:28:05.141 --> 00:28:06.059 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Ready.</i>

450
00:28:06.142 --> 00:28:08.728 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Do you show a record
of an inmate named Dekon Elig?

451
00:28:08.812 --> 00:28:10.271 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Affirmative.</i>

452
00:28:10.855 --> 00:28:12.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Biographical data.

453
00:28:12.565 --> 00:28:14.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dekon Elig, geneticist.</i>

454
00:28:14.651 --> 00:28:18.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

455
00:28:18.655 --> 00:28:22.492 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Killed while attempting escape,</i>
<i>Stardate 39355.</i>

456
00:28:23.034 --> 00:28:24.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Certificate of Death on file.</i>

457
00:28:26.037 --> 00:28:27.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No need to ask how you're doing.

458
00:28:27.956 --> 00:28:29.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Chasing after ghosts.

459
00:28:29.666 --> 00:28:31.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have 12 hours to catch one.

460
00:28:32.377 --> 00:28:33.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And then?

461
00:28:33.503 --> 00:28:34.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
People start dying.

462
00:28:41.094 --> 00:28:42.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer...

463
00:28:45.098 --> 00:28:47.392 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
display Dekon Elig's Certificate of Death.

464
00:28:49.185 --> 00:28:51.604 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Identify signature of witness.

465
00:28:51.688 --> 00:28:54.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[woman]<i> Certificate of Death</i>
<i>was witnessed by Surmak Ren,</i>

466
00:28:54.774 --> 00:28:57.110 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Bajoran medical assistant.</i>

467
00:28:58.027 --> 00:29:01.406 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Show me biographical data on Surmak Ren.

468
00:29:01.489 --> 00:29:02.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren.</i>

469
00:29:03.158 --> 00:29:07.370 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Former member of the Higa Metar sect</i>
<i>of the Bajoran underground.</i>

470
00:29:07.454 --> 00:29:09.622 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Repatriated to Bajor upon closing</i>

471
00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:14.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>of the Velos VII Internment Camp,</i>
<i>Stardate 46302.</i>

472
00:29:14.377 --> 00:29:16.129 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Current status unknown.</i>

473
00:29:18.089 --> 00:29:21.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking whir]

474
00:29:21.134 --> 00:29:23.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking slows]

475
00:29:27.640 --> 00:29:28.892 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[clicking stops]

476
00:29:28.975 --> 00:29:30.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

477
00:29:36.816 --> 00:29:38.151 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any luck?

478
00:29:38.443 --> 00:29:41.237 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I haven't won a spin in hours.

479
00:29:42.655 --> 00:29:44.491 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh, care to place a friendly wager?

480
00:29:45.784 --> 00:29:48.244 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If it's your reputation
you're thinking about,

481
00:29:48.328 --> 00:29:49.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
no one need ever know.

482
00:29:49.913 --> 00:29:52.582 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It has nothing to do with my reputation.

483
00:29:53.666 --> 00:29:55.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighs]

484
00:29:55.335 --> 00:29:57.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The truth is, I never...

485
00:29:59.130 --> 00:30:00.423 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
learned the game.

486
00:30:00.799 --> 00:30:02.592 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You mean, you've sat here
for all these years

487
00:30:02.675 --> 00:30:04.552 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and you don't even know how to gamble?

488
00:30:04.844 --> 00:30:06.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's correct.

489
00:30:06.763 --> 00:30:09.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No wonder you always look so bored.

490
00:30:10.433 --> 00:30:12.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The rules are quite simple, actually.

491
00:30:12.519 --> 00:30:14.813 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'd be happy to show them to you.

492
00:30:15.480 --> 00:30:17.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Some other time, perhaps.

493
00:30:17.565 --> 00:30:19.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko needs me in Ops.

494
00:30:19.526 --> 00:30:23.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
And, since the entire security force
has been stricken with aphasia

495
00:30:23.530 --> 00:30:26.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the Promenade is in
a very vulnerable position.

496
00:30:26.908 --> 00:30:28.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How unfortunate.

497
00:30:29.953 --> 00:30:32.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Consider it a warning, Quark.

498
00:30:33.957 --> 00:30:37.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Because I'm holding you
personally responsible

499
00:30:37.126 --> 00:30:39.712 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
if anything turns up missing.

500
00:30:40.713 --> 00:30:42.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Is that understood?

501
00:30:42.966 --> 00:30:44.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perfectly.

502
00:30:44.634 --> 00:30:45.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hmm.

503
00:30:54.561 --> 00:30:55.812 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dabo.

504
00:30:57.063 --> 00:31:00.525 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, analyze test sample 37 delta.

505
00:31:00.859 --> 00:31:03.278 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Detail effects on viral containment.

506
00:31:03.361 --> 00:31:05.864 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Working.</i>
<i>Analysis complete.</i>

507
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:08.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Sample 37 delta ineffective.</i>

508
00:31:08.908 --> 00:31:11.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Viral protein sheath is unaffected.</i>

509
00:31:11.452 --> 00:31:14.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Nucleotide sequence remains intact.</i>

510
00:31:16.499 --> 00:31:19.669 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, replay morning.

511
00:31:19.752 --> 00:31:22.630 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

512
00:31:26.301 --> 00:31:30.096 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Glass lunch judge a bin to let it.

513
00:31:30.179 --> 00:31:32.974 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Command unclear. Please repeat.</i>

514
00:31:45.778 --> 00:31:49.866 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, establish a link
with the Bajoran Medical Index

515
00:31:49.949 --> 00:31:53.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
for the, uh, Northwestern District.

516
00:31:53.536 --> 00:31:55.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Link established.</i>

517
00:31:55.121 --> 00:31:58.082 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Access all information on Dr. Surmak Ren.

518
00:31:58.541 --> 00:32:01.294 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>There are no records matching that name.</i>

519
00:32:01.711 --> 00:32:03.963 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try the Northeastern District--
same search.

520
00:32:04.589 --> 00:32:06.716 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[female voice on computer]
<i>Dr. Surmak Ren, currently serving</i>

521
00:32:06.799 --> 00:32:10.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>as Chief Administrator</i>
<i>of the Ilvian Medical Complex.</i>

522
00:32:10.470 --> 00:32:13.640 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Computer, open a channel
to the Ilvian Medical Complex

523
00:32:13.723 --> 00:32:15.516 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Administrator's office.

524
00:32:17.560 --> 00:32:20.021 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>This is Dr. Surmak. And you are?</i>

525
00:32:20.104 --> 00:32:23.691 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major Kira Nerys,
Bajoran liaison to Deep Space 9.

526
00:32:23.775 --> 00:32:26.694 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Ah, yes, the old Cardassian</i>
<i>mining station.</i>

527
00:32:26.778 --> 00:32:28.071 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>How can I help you?</i>

528
00:32:28.154 --> 00:32:29.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It depends.

529
00:32:29.572 --> 00:32:30.907 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>On what?</i>

530
00:32:31.366 --> 00:32:33.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
On whether or not you helped Dekon Elig

531
00:32:33.534 --> 00:32:35.954 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
plant an aphasia virus here 18 years ago.

532
00:32:36.579 --> 00:32:39.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have no idea what you're talking about.</i>

533
00:32:42.794 --> 00:32:45.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, Sisko, I'm a security officer--
a good one--

534
00:32:45.463 --> 00:32:48.132 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but that doesn't make me qualified
to help you run station operations.

535
00:32:48.216 --> 00:32:49.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're probably right, Constable.

536
00:32:49.759 --> 00:32:52.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But, as you can see,
you're all I've got.

537
00:32:52.804 --> 00:32:54.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Commander...

538
00:32:55.682 --> 00:32:59.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Commander, I think I found our scientist.

539
00:32:59.102 --> 00:33:00.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Does he have an antidote?
-I don't know.

540
00:33:00.728 --> 00:33:02.689 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He broke the connection
the minute I mentioned the virus.

541
00:33:02.772 --> 00:33:04.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, you mind telling me
where you're going?

542
00:33:04.941 --> 00:33:08.444 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
To continue my conversation
with Dr. Surmak, in person.

543
00:33:08.528 --> 00:33:10.947 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Major, I can't allow you
to break quarantine.

544
00:33:11.030 --> 00:33:12.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can't risk
spreading the virus to Bajor.

545
00:33:12.573 --> 00:33:14.075 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am well aware of that, Commander.

546
00:33:14.158 --> 00:33:17.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
As a matter of fact,
I don't intend to step foot on the planet.

547
00:33:18.162 --> 00:33:19.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Better let her go, Sisko.

548
00:33:21.499 --> 00:33:23.042 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
She's all we've got.

549
00:33:34.846 --> 00:33:38.182 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Let's just hope there's someone left
to greet her when she returns.

550
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:54.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jake.

551
00:33:55.992 --> 00:33:57.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How's it going?

552
00:34:10.882 --> 00:34:12.675 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've missed you.

553
00:34:13.509 --> 00:34:16.054 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I know things don't look
too good right now,

554
00:34:16.512 --> 00:34:18.264 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but they'll get better.

555
00:34:19.098 --> 00:34:21.225 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You have to believe that...

556
00:34:22.435 --> 00:34:25.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
because I'm not going
to lose you, Jake.

557
00:34:26.064 --> 00:34:27.523 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You hear me?

558
00:34:28.232 --> 00:34:30.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not going to lose you.

559
00:34:46.084 --> 00:34:47.376 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You better take a look at this.

560
00:34:47.460 --> 00:34:49.295 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We have activity on Docking Port 5.

561
00:34:49.378 --> 00:34:50.880 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think a ship is about to depart.

562
00:34:50.963 --> 00:34:52.882 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Docking Port 5? That's Jaheel's ship.

563
00:34:52.965 --> 00:34:54.425 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Put him on screen.

564
00:34:59.555 --> 00:35:02.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, your ship has
not been cleared for departure.

565
00:35:03.101 --> 00:35:04.435 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The mooring clamps are locked,

566
00:35:04.519 --> 00:35:06.646 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I don't intend to release them.

567
00:35:06.729 --> 00:35:08.981 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I suggest you change your mind.</i>

568
00:35:09.107 --> 00:35:11.651 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I'm taking aft thrusters to one half.</i>

569
00:35:14.946 --> 00:35:18.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Captain, cut your engines
before you rip your ship apart.

570
00:35:19.450 --> 00:35:20.993 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He's not reducing power.

571
00:35:21.536 --> 00:35:24.664 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Jaheel, I'm ordering you to stand down.

572
00:35:24.747 --> 00:35:26.916 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Your orders are no concern of mine.</i>

573
00:35:26.999 --> 00:35:29.919 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>My entire crew has been</i>
<i>confined to your hospital.</i>

574
00:35:30.002 --> 00:35:32.922 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>I must leave now</i>
<i>while I can still function.</i>

575
00:35:33.005 --> 00:35:37.135 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I understand that you're frightened
but believe me, you're better off here.

576
00:35:37.218 --> 00:35:40.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You don't want to be out there alone
and get hit by the virus.

577
00:35:40.096 --> 00:35:42.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Don't worry about me, I'm fine.</i>

578
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:46.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>And I plan to stay that way.</i>

579
00:35:46.561 --> 00:35:48.563 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-And if you think you're go--
-[cuts transmission]

580
00:35:50.940 --> 00:35:52.316 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll have to retract the clamps.

581
00:35:52.400 --> 00:35:56.487 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Once he's clear of the station
we can grab him with a tractor beam.

582
00:36:03.035 --> 00:36:04.662 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Damn.
-What's wrong?

583
00:36:04.787 --> 00:36:06.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's too much stress
on the mooring clamps.

584
00:36:06.664 --> 00:36:08.040 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're not retracting.

585
00:36:08.624 --> 00:36:10.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groaning]

586
00:36:11.043 --> 00:36:13.462 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[console beeping]

587
00:36:14.130 --> 00:36:16.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His aft isolation plate buckled.

588
00:36:17.133 --> 00:36:19.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
His main power core's been ruptured.

589
00:36:19.552 --> 00:36:22.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If the internal fuel cells collapse,
the whole ship will explode.

590
00:36:22.597 --> 00:36:25.141 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And take half the docking ring with it.

591
00:36:35.943 --> 00:36:37.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Computer, isolate a com line

592
00:36:37.778 --> 00:36:41.073 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
to the Ilvian Medical Complex
Administrator's office.

593
00:36:41.157 --> 00:36:42.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[female voice on computer]<i> Line isolated.</i>

594
00:36:43.075 --> 00:36:44.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Scan office for life-forms.

595
00:36:45.077 --> 00:36:47.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>One life-form present.</i>

596
00:36:47.747 --> 00:36:50.249 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lock on and stand by to transport.

597
00:36:52.793 --> 00:36:55.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-This is Dr. Surmak.</i>
-Hello again, Doctor.

598
00:36:55.588 --> 00:36:57.465 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just checking to see
you're in your office.

599
00:36:58.007 --> 00:36:59.467 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>I have nothing to say to you--</i>

600
00:37:07.308 --> 00:37:09.101 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hello again, Doctor.

601
00:37:09.435 --> 00:37:11.270 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is outrageous.

602
00:37:11.354 --> 00:37:14.023 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I demand you return me
to my office immediately.

603
00:37:14.106 --> 00:37:16.859 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax, Doctor. You won't be gone long.

604
00:37:22.365 --> 00:37:25.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Try to reestablish visual contact
with Jaheel's ship.

605
00:37:27.787 --> 00:37:29.914 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] No response. His com lines are down.

606
00:37:30.122 --> 00:37:32.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bypass communications
through a secondary grid.

607
00:37:33.000 --> 00:37:35.544 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See if you can switch
to external pickups.

608
00:37:35.920 --> 00:37:36.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Got it.

609
00:37:39.715 --> 00:37:42.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
His fire control systems
don't appear to be working.

610
00:37:43.511 --> 00:37:47.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have about 15 minutes
before the fuel cells collapse.

611
00:37:48.557 --> 00:37:50.851 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I hope you feel better than you look.

612
00:37:51.477 --> 00:37:53.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Must be that damn virus.

613
00:37:54.146 --> 00:37:55.773 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This is Sisko.

614
00:37:56.315 --> 00:37:59.777 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Any station personnel who can understand
what I'm saying, come to Ops immediately.

615
00:37:59.860 --> 00:38:01.404 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need help up here.

616
00:38:01.487 --> 00:38:03.698 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We have to get that ship
away from the station.

617
00:38:03.990 --> 00:38:05.992 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't we explode
the mooring clamps?

618
00:38:06.075 --> 00:38:08.577 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The blast should push the ship
away from the docking ring.

619
00:38:08.786 --> 00:38:10.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We'll have to get down there
and blow it manually.

620
00:38:11.330 --> 00:38:12.748 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[groans]

621
00:38:12.832 --> 00:38:14.166 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll do it.

622
00:38:15.293 --> 00:38:16.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

623
00:38:17.169 --> 00:38:18.504 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You can cross barrels.

624
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:21.340 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All job appalled.

625
00:38:22.174 --> 00:38:23.259 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What was that?

626
00:38:25.052 --> 00:38:26.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Bread...

627
00:38:26.304 --> 00:38:27.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
the arrive...

628
00:38:27.847 --> 00:38:29.807 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
seen earlier.

629
00:38:31.642 --> 00:38:33.894 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I see.

630
00:38:43.070 --> 00:38:44.905 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Major, this is kidnapping.

631
00:38:44.989 --> 00:38:47.199 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Turn this ship around
or I swear you will spend

632
00:38:47.325 --> 00:38:49.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
the rest of your life
in Kran-Tobol Prison.

633
00:38:49.910 --> 00:38:53.205 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Fine. But first, we need your help.

634
00:38:53.331 --> 00:38:56.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The aphasia virus is spreading
through the station.

635
00:38:56.083 --> 00:38:57.543 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why come to me?

636
00:38:57.877 --> 00:38:59.628 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You helped create the virus, didn't you?

637
00:38:59.837 --> 00:39:01.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, I had practically
nothing to do with it.

638
00:39:01.964 --> 00:39:03.883 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon Elig created the virus.

639
00:39:03.966 --> 00:39:05.885 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I was merely his medical assistant.

640
00:39:06.218 --> 00:39:08.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That seems like a lifetime ago now.

641
00:39:08.554 --> 00:39:10.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was only in the underground
for six months

642
00:39:10.765 --> 00:39:12.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
before we were captured.

643
00:39:12.350 --> 00:39:14.226 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not responsible for this.

644
00:39:14.352 --> 00:39:15.978 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I am not looking to place blame!

645
00:39:16.062 --> 00:39:18.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All I want is the antidote.

646
00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:20.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know of any antidote.

647
00:39:21.025 --> 00:39:23.402 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If Dekon created one, he never told me.

648
00:39:23.486 --> 00:39:24.779 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Listen, Surmak.

649
00:39:25.112 --> 00:39:27.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I have a station full of dying people

650
00:39:27.198 --> 00:39:30.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and you are the closest thing there is
to an expert on this virus.

651
00:39:31.160 --> 00:39:32.787 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I sympathize, Major,

652
00:39:32.870 --> 00:39:34.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but I don't think I can help you.

653
00:39:35.873 --> 00:39:37.083 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

654
00:39:38.709 --> 00:39:40.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then how about helping yourself?

655
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:42.505 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning what?

656
00:39:43.047 --> 00:39:44.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Meaning...

657
00:39:45.549 --> 00:39:48.761 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've been infected
with your virus, Doctor...

658
00:39:50.388 --> 00:39:52.556 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
so now you're infected, too.

659
00:39:58.062 --> 00:40:00.940 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
To anyone who can hear me, this is Odo.

660
00:40:01.023 --> 00:40:02.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sisko's infected.

661
00:40:02.149 --> 00:40:04.276 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I could really use some help here in Ops.

662
00:40:04.402 --> 00:40:08.030 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do I detect a note of panic in your voice?

663
00:40:08.114 --> 00:40:09.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark.

664
00:40:09.782 --> 00:40:13.160 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I to believe that you're
volunteering to help?

665
00:40:13.244 --> 00:40:15.621 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Who said anything about volunteering?

666
00:40:15.704 --> 00:40:18.207 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can haggle over price later.

667
00:40:18.290 --> 00:40:19.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now, um...

668
00:40:20.167 --> 00:40:22.586 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
how may I be of use?

669
00:40:23.045 --> 00:40:25.297 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I need to get to Docking Port 5 now.

670
00:40:25.381 --> 00:40:27.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in five minutes.

671
00:40:28.217 --> 00:40:29.468 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll beam you over.

672
00:40:29.718 --> 00:40:31.929 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You?
-Relax.

673
00:40:32.012 --> 00:40:35.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I served on a Ferengi freighter
for eight years.

674
00:40:36.976 --> 00:40:38.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
All right.

675
00:40:38.853 --> 00:40:42.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I must have witnessed the procedure
hundreds of times.

676
00:40:42.523 --> 00:40:46.318 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Witnessed? You mean to say you never
handled the controls yourself?

677
00:40:46.444 --> 00:40:47.778 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Energizing!

678
00:40:55.286 --> 00:40:56.745 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[sighing]

679
00:41:06.589 --> 00:41:09.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Kira to Ops. Approaching Landing Pad 7.

680
00:41:09.341 --> 00:41:11.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Request clearance
to initiate docking procedure.

681
00:41:11.760 --> 00:41:14.555 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
[Quark]<i> Welcome back.</i>
<i>I could use some help up here.</i>

682
00:41:14.638 --> 00:41:17.266 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Quark, what are you doing in Ops?

683
00:41:17.766 --> 00:41:19.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[laughing]

684
00:41:23.647 --> 00:41:24.857 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
First thing I need to see

685
00:41:24.940 --> 00:41:27.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is your doctor's viral
characterization research.

686
00:41:31.489 --> 00:41:33.282 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He was beginning to develop
an antidote series.

687
00:41:33.365 --> 00:41:34.825 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's take a look at that.

688
00:41:34.909 --> 00:41:36.702 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Kira] Listen, Doctor, um...

689
00:41:36.785 --> 00:41:37.870 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll be in Ops.

690
00:41:37.953 --> 00:41:40.331 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you need me, use this string impact.

691
00:41:41.290 --> 00:41:43.125 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lot show red intense.

692
00:41:44.502 --> 00:41:47.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think you'd better sit down, Major.

693
00:41:51.133 --> 00:41:53.677 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm wailing]

694
00:42:06.398 --> 00:42:09.235 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Jaheel] Dog fellow distance.

695
00:42:09.318 --> 00:42:10.903 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Odo] Yeah, tell me about it.

696
00:42:10.986 --> 00:42:13.072 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo, you'd better hurry up.</i>

697
00:42:13.155 --> 00:42:15.407 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That ship's going to explode
in one minute.

698
00:42:18.869 --> 00:42:20.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Virum protein sheath.

699
00:42:21.580 --> 00:42:23.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nucleotide sequence.

700
00:42:24.250 --> 00:42:25.251 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yes.

701
00:42:25.334 --> 00:42:26.418 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's right.

702
00:42:26.502 --> 00:42:28.754 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's an adaptive, synaptic inhibitor.

703
00:42:29.338 --> 00:42:30.756 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Dekon was brilliant.

704
00:42:30.839 --> 00:42:32.424 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No doubt of that.

705
00:42:32.550 --> 00:42:36.011 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think we've found your antidote, Major.

706
00:42:38.681 --> 00:42:40.391 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> 40 seconds.</i>

707
00:42:53.737 --> 00:42:55.114 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
30 seconds. Hurry!

708
00:42:55.447 --> 00:42:57.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I know, I know.

709
00:43:01.829 --> 00:43:03.706 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
20 seconds!

710
00:43:09.420 --> 00:43:11.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ten seconds!

711
00:43:11.422 --> 00:43:13.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[alarm blares]

712
00:43:13.340 --> 00:43:14.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[gasps]

713
00:43:36.363 --> 00:43:38.240 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Quark]<i> Odo? Quark to Odo.</i>

714
00:43:38.365 --> 00:43:39.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You still with us?

715
00:43:40.242 --> 00:43:42.453 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Try not to sound too disappointed.

716
00:43:42.786 --> 00:43:46.081 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Now, about that little matter
of my hazard pay...

717
00:43:46.874 --> 00:43:48.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why, you...

718
00:43:52.838 --> 00:43:54.923 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Come on.

719
00:43:58.886 --> 00:44:02.848 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
[Sisko]<i> Station Log, Stardate 46425.8.</i>

720
00:44:02.931 --> 00:44:04.600 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>With the help of Dr. Bashir's notes,</i>

721
00:44:04.683 --> 00:44:08.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>Dr. Surmak was able to find</i>
<i>an antidote for the aphasia virus.</i>

722
00:44:08.228 --> 00:44:11.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We are continuing to administer</i>
<i>it throughout the station</i>

723
00:44:11.357 --> 00:44:14.068 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>and things are slowly</i>
<i>returning to normal.</i>

724
00:44:14.151 --> 00:44:15.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Good to have you back, Chief.

725
00:44:15.819 --> 00:44:17.279 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Thank you, sir.

726
00:44:17.363 --> 00:44:18.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Coffee, black.

727
00:44:25.788 --> 00:44:26.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
O'Brien!

